<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,847,1183]" box="[198,1174,925,951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,925,951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Southwest 
<collectingCountry box="[520,622,925,951]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[748,843,925,951]" name="Uganda" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Uganda</collectingCountry>
. TDWG: 24 ETH; 25 UGA.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,847,1183]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,427,963,989]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Characteristics:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[428,628,964,989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neoleroyi">
<emphasis box="[428,628,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Coffea neoleroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other African 
<taxonomicName box="[1019,1195,964,990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1019,1097,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Coffea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="J.D.Hooker, 1873" authorityName="J.D.Hooker" authorityYear="1873" box="[151,278,1002,1027]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,278,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Psilanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its small obovate leaves (apex rounded), and from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bridson)" authorityName="A.P.Davis" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Bridson" box="[940,1179,1002,1028]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semsei">
<emphasis box="[940,1056,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">C. semsei</emphasis>
(Bridson)
</taxonomicName>
A.P.Davis by having rounded (vs. distinctly apiculate) calyculi lobes and pedicellate fruits (vs. sessile). Further morphological information for this species can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Leroy, J. - F." box="[668,824,1080,1106]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="251 - 258" refId="ref3042" refString="Leroy, J. - F. (1981) Les cafeiers du genre Psilanthus (Rubiacees) en Afrique orientale et en Asie et iles du Pacifique. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle. 4 e Serie Section B, Adansonia Botanique Phytochimie 3: 251 - 258." type="journal article" year="1981">Leroy (1981)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bridson, D. M." box="[880,1062,1080,1106]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="817 - 860" refId="ref2063" refString="Bridson, D. M. (1982) Studies in Coffea and Psilanthus for part 2 of ' Flora of Tropical East Africa': Rubiaceae. Kew Bulletin 36: 817 - 860." type="journal article" year="1982">Bridson (1982)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,847,1183]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,277,1118,1144]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Notes:</emphasis>
—A new name is required for this species as there is already a 
<taxonomicName box="[1077,1252,1118,1144]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1077,1155,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Coffea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with the same specific epithet: 
<taxonomicName authority="J.D.Hooker, 1873" authorityName="Bridson" authorityYear="1982" box="[344,446,1157,1182]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leroyi">
<emphasis box="[344,446,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">C. leroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A.P. Davis (
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, A. P. &amp; Rakotonasolo, F." box="[593,933,1157,1183]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="405 - 416" refId="ref2273" refString="Davis, A. P. &amp; Rakotonasolo, F. (2000. Three New Species of Coffea L. (Rubiaceae) from Madagascar. Kew Bulletin 55: 405 - 416." type="journal article" year="2000">Davis &amp; Rakotonasolo 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
